<TITLE> Mobile operators join illegal VoIP drive </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 4 (bdnerws24.com)  Mobile-phone operators have joined telecoms regulator BTRC and elite anticrime force Rapid Action Battalion in their drive against illegal VoIP business. "Active participation of the mobile-phone operators has strengthened the drive against the illegal VoIP. Thousands of SIM cards being used for the unlawful activities have been blocked already," the BTRC said in a press statement on Wednesday. The BTRC said due to illicit VoIP activities, government had been counting crores in lost revenues. The IGW, ICX and IIG firms, licensed under the government's ILDS policy, are in trouble, the statement observed. A meeting was held on VoIP between representatives from the cellphone operators and BTRC officials at BTRC office on Wednesday. Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission chairman retired major general Manzurul Alam said, "The RAB cooperation in the anti-VoIP drive is commendable." "It has now become more forceful with the mobile-phone operators joining us in the campaign." "Allout cooperation is important to prevent the illegal activities in the telecoms sector," he pointed out. bd
